  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Enhancing Teacher Professional Development (TPD) and Teacher Roles in ensuring Educational Alignment</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The programme aims at promoting evidence-based teacher policies and promising practices in the light of SDG4 goals, with an emphasis on innovative and effective TPD strategies. It will equally encourage teacher reflective practice with emphasis on the transformative roles of teachers as models for promoting and implementing GE and other SDG4 goals. They will be also empowered to use gender lenses (as well as other SDG4-related &quot;lenses&quot;) in assessing and improving curricula, textbooks, and classroom practices from the perspective of enhancing educational alignment. 
The Programme will provide equally customized support to MoEs and specialized Teacher agencies in Lebanon and Syria in the context of Education in Crisis.</narrative>
  </description>
